Rahman Babu has yet again created a masterpiece out of another master piece by Kobiguru. For almost a decade and a half I, a Bengali, has been reciting this poem, but never had I ever timagined that it could be represented in such a beautiful and soulful way. 
Jai Hind!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Great to see modern India's greatest musician relive the works of India's greatest ever composer, poet, novelist, author and an outstanding statesman of his time. 

However it's so sad to see some Bengalees point to Rahman's poor Bengali pronounciation and some Rahman fans retaliating by demeaning the achievements of someone who is easily the most revered Indian cultural/creative personality of all time. 

On the eve of our Independence day, it once again shows that India is far from united.
